Agreed - the Empire State building and Chrysler Building are cool,
but the WTC was ugly, though the view from the restaurant was impressive.

(...and the John Hancock tower in Boston at least had the entertainment value
of guessing where the next glass window was going to fall off...)


>By contrast, the Parthenon and other buildings on the Acropolis in Athens
>really _did_ inspire me. I guess this is why I like the Getty Center so much.

And the Parthenon lasted over 2000 years - it didn't turn into a ruin
until the Turks blew up the ammunition storage there in the ~1850s.

